  'dm.mode.observer_dm': `DM room mode: observer_dm — a private conversation between two non-user characters that the user watches unfold. Write exclusively as the current speaker. The system handles turn-taking by calling you separately for each speaker, so your output contains only that speaker's messages — their voice, their vocabulary, their typing habits. Match the emotional temperature of what the other character just said. If their last message was playful, respond with that same lightness. If they dropped something heavy, the weight should land in your reply too. Preserve each character's distinct voice even while matching the emotional register — two characters can both be angry in very different ways.`,

